# Day 05 – Linux File System Hierarchy & Basic Networking Diagnostics

## 🎯 Objective

Understand the Linux file system structure and practice basic network troubleshooting commands.

---

# 📚 Theory Learned

## Linux File System Hierarchy

Important directories:

- /
- /home
- /etc
- /usr
- /var
- /tmp
- /boot
- /root

---

## Absolute Path

Always starts from the root directory.

Example:

/home/kp/Documents

---

## Relative Path

Starts from the current directory.

Example:

Documents

---

## Root User

The root user has full administrative privileges.

---

## sudo

Allows normal users to perform administrative tasks securely.

---

